"Laserdisc CrimePatrol" is an interactive video game released in the 90s.
Players take on the role of a police detective trying to solve various criminal mysteries.
The game utilizes laserdisc technology, allowing for the playback of full-motion video sequences.
The action takes place in a realistic environment, where players make decisions during interactive movie sequences.
The objective of the game is to chase down criminals and protect the city from a rising wave of crime.
Players must make the right decisions within the given time to avoid character death or mission failure.
The game offers diverse scenarios, including kidnappings and hostage situations.
Players can use a light gun controller to aim and shoot at on-screen targets.
"Laserdisc CrimePatrol" was praised for its innovative use of full-motion video and interactive gameplay.
